Anomalous diffusion of monomers after two DSBs

Ignacio Madrid

June 26, 2018

Anomalous diffusion keeping and removing CLs in the DF

The anomalous diffusion exponent \(\alpha\) was extraited from the trajectories of each one of the 100 monomers of the polymer after the induction of two fixed DSBs at \(A_1 = 46\) and \(B_1 = 54\) (the first monomers is numerated \(1\)). The break is followed by the removal or not of the CLs in the DF, and finally a waiting relaxation time of 10000 steps (50 seconds) before start tracking the monomers position. The same is performed for different values of \(N_c\) between 2 and 58. \(N_d = 3\) CLs were imposed in the DF to compare both scenarios.
